The {{strftime}} function in [puppetlabs-stdlib|https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppetlabs-stdlib/blob/72f6e379a647396c276d7f216b307361ac76f376/lib/puppet/parser/functions/strftime.rb] and the new {{strftime}} function added as part of PUP-5871 are not compatible. The one from stdlib has the following API:
{code:puppet}
String strftime(String format, String timezone = undef)
{code}
whereas the API of the new function is:
{code:puppet}
String strftime(Variant[Timespan,Timestamp], String format)
{code}

As part of this change, a third optional timezone argument should also be added, to allow the given time to be formatted in accordance with that timezone.

