We still use the hiera version 3 (i.e. unversioned/classic) hiera.yaml format.

With puppet 4.8.x and older versions class parameter lookups in hiera had the default merge behavior 'first', even if the option 'merge_behavior' 'deep' was active. With puppet 4.9.x class parameters of type array are now merged if the option 'merge_behavior' 'deep' is active.

A simple reproducer:

{code:title=hiera.yaml}
---
:backends:
  - yaml
:hierarchy:
  - lvl1
  - lvl2

:yaml:
  :datadir: "."

:merge_behavior: deep
{code}

{code:title=lvl1.yaml}
tclass::test:
  - lvl1
{code}

{code:title=lvl2.yaml}
tclass::test:
  - lvl2
{code}

{code:title=test.pp}
class tclass (
  $test = false,
) {
  notice($test)
}

include tclass
{code}

with puppet 4.9.3:
{noformat}
puppet apply --hiera_config=hiera.yaml test.pp
Notice: Scope(Class[Tclass]): [lvl1, lvl2]
{noformat}

with puppet 4.8.0:
{noformat}
puppet apply --hiera_config=hiera.yaml test.pp
Notice: Scope(Class[Tclass]): [lvl1]
{noformat}

if merge_behavior deep is removed from hiera.yaml, then puppet 4.9.3 behaves like puppet 4.8.0.

